Question for the learning objective "understand what a basic inline style is in Cascading Style Sheets"

When css is used inside an html element using the style attribute it is called:
(Ex. <h1 style="color: red;">Header</h1>)

  !- Inline style
    Inline CSS allows you to apply a unique style to one HTML element at a time. You assign CSS to a specific HTML tag by using the style attribute with any CSS properties defined within it.
    https://www.bitdegree.org/learn/inline-css
  External style
	   This is the more desirable method, especially on bigger projects. However, it is done through a different file, not in the html itself.
	  https://www.quackit.com/css/external_style_sheets.cfm
  Inline citation
	   Inline citation is used in writing academic papers. Web development uses inline styling.
     https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_css.asp
  Lazy
		In general, it is not considered a best practice. However, there are times when inline styles are the right (or only) choice.
		https://www.codecademy.com/articles/html-inline-styles


Question for the learning objective "understand when to use inline styles and when not to use inline styles"

Why do most professional dev teams prefer styles in an external stylesheet rather than internal or inline?

  It’s cacheable
    Almost. External stylesheets are cached, and aren’t reloaded every time you visit a page, we don’t have to update 1000’s of pages’ styles to change a button, an author doesn’t have to go fiddling with the web application to change a button.
    https://www.bitdegree.org/learn/inline-css
  It’s distributed
    Almost. External stylesheets are cached, and aren’t reloaded every time you visit a page, we don’t have to update 1000’s of pages’ styles to change a button, an author doesn’t have to go fiddling with the web application to change a button.
    https://www.bitdegree.org/learn/inline-css
  It separates concerns
	  Almost. External stylesheets are cached, and aren’t reloaded every time you visit a page, we don’t have to update 1000’s of pages’ styles to change a button, an author doesn’t have to go fiddling with the web application to change a button.
    https://www.bitdegree.org/learn/inline-css
  !- All of the above
	  Correct! External stylesheets are cached, and aren’t reloaded every time you visit a page, we don’t have to update 1000’s of pages’ styles to change a button, an author doesn’t have to go fiddling with the web application to change a button.
	  https://www.bitdegree.org/learn/inline-css
